 Project Overview
This project provides an **in-depth analysis of IPL (Indian Premier League)** data using **Power BI** to uncover insights related to player performance, team statistics, and match outcomes.

The interactive dashboard helps fans, analysts, and data enthusiasts explore:
- Team and player performance trends  
- Match results and season summaries  
- Batting, bowling, and win/loss patterns  
- Key factors influencing match outcomes  

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives
- Analyze IPL data to track **team and player performance** across seasons.  
- Compare **batting and bowling statistics** to identify top performers.  
- Understand **venue-based trends**, toss outcomes, and match results.  
- Build a visually rich **Power BI dashboard** with dynamic filters and KPIs.  
- Provide actionable insights for sports analytics and decision-making.

---

## ğŸ“Š Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
| KPI | Description |
|-----|--------------|
| **Total Matches** | Total number of IPL matches played |
| **Total Runs Scored** | Cumulative runs across all matches |
| **Top Run Scorer** | Player with the highest total runs |
| **Top Wicket Taker** | Bowler with the most wickets |
| **Most Wins (Team)** | Team with the highest match wins |
| **Toss Impact %** | Correlation between toss win and match win |
| **Average Score per Match** | Mean runs scored per team per match |

---

## ğŸ§  Insights & Findings
- **Mumbai Indians (MI)** and **Chennai Super Kings (CSK)** are the most consistent teams with high win percentages.  
- **Toss-winning teams** have a slightly higher chance of winning matches, especially while chasing.  
- **Virat Kohli** and **David Warner** lead in career total runs.  
- **Lasith Malinga** and **Yuzvendra Chahal** top the wicket charts.  
- **Eden Gardens** and **Wankhede Stadium** record the highest average scores.  
- **Powerplay overs (1â€“6)** heavily influence match outcomes.  

